---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="hero">
				<h1>üéôÔ∏è My Weird Prompts</h1>
				<p class="tagline">Random questions voiced throughout daily life, transformed into multimodal content</p>
			</div>

			<div class="content">
				<section class="intro">
					<h2>What is this?</h2>
					<p>
						Ever have a random question pop into your head while doing the dishes, walking the dog, or trying to fall asleep?
						That's what this project is all about. I capture these spontaneous prompts using my voice, send them through
						an AI processing pipeline, and turn them into full blog posts complete with audio episodes and AI-generated responses.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="how-it-works">
					<h2>How It Works</h2>
					<ol>
						<li><strong>Voice Capture:</strong> I record a question or prompt using the Voicenotes app</li>
						<li><strong>AI Processing:</strong> My voice is transcribed and cleaned up by Gemini Pro 2.5</li>
						<li><strong>Response Generation:</strong> Claude Sonnet 4.5 generates a comprehensive response</li>
						<li><strong>Audio Creation:</strong> The response is converted to speech and combined with my original voice recording</li>
						<li><strong>Publication:</strong> Everything is automatically published here with images, audio, and text</li>
					</ol>
				</section>

				<section class="why">
					<h2>Why?</h2>
					<p>
						There's a gap in AI tooling for preserving and sharing interesting LLM outputs. This is my experiment in:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Building a personal knowledge base of AI-assisted insights</li>
						<li>Creating multimodal content from voice-first interactions</li>
						<li>Exploring the future of human-AI collaboration</li>
						<li>Making weird, random questions into something useful (or at least interesting)</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="disclaimer">
					<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Fair Warning</h2>
					<p>
						This content is AI-generated. While I do curate and review posts, some responses may be incomplete,
						inaccurate, or just plain weird. That's part of the experiment! Think of this as a public digital
						garden where AI and human thinking intersect in unexpected ways.
					</p>
				</section>

				<div class="cta">
					<a href="/blog" class="button">Browse the Prompts ‚Üí</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
		<style>
			.hero {
				text-align: center;
				padding: 3rem 1rem;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
				color: white;
				border-radius: 16px;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}

			.hero h1 {
				font-size: 3rem;
				margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
			}

			.tagline {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				opacity: 0.95;
				max-width: 700px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}

			.content {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 1rem;
			}

			section {
				margin: 3rem 0;
			}

			section h2 {
				color: rgb(var(--accent));
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			ol, ul {
				line-height: 1.8;
			}

			ol li, ul li {
				margin: 0.75rem 0;
			}

			.disclaimer {
				background: #fff3cd;
				border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
			}

			.cta {
				text-align: center;
				margin: 4rem 0;
			}

			.button {
				display: inline-block;
				padding: 1rem 2rem;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
				color: white;
				text-decoration: none;
				border-radius: 8px;
				font-weight: 600;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
				box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
			}

			.button:hover {
				transform: translateY(-2px);
				box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
			}

			@media (max-width: 720px) {
				.hero h1 {
					font-size: 2rem;
				}

				.tagline {
					font-size: 1rem;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
